antiphonic (AN-ti-PHON-ic), adj. The presence of an antiphon between two choirs with a call and a response in song or in chant, usually in the form of a hymn or a psalm.<br>

'''The Antiphonic Music Company'''<br>
Antiphonic is an online Christian music company, started by [[Kelson Herr]], with the sole purpose of providing underground Christian music of all genres to music lovers around the world.

